{"title":"- Tiroiditis Subaguda","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/- Tiroiditis Subaguda.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Tiroiditis\\NSubaguda","guid":"GDzDKPbW_n5d4W7Q9MSANA","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Definición ","guid":"gMkYHPxawaBjqFXywDV0CA","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"Enfermedad inflamatoria rara y autolimitada de la glándula tiroides","guid":"cKzDIiSqmbfuEibYYpM6Cw","children":[]},{"id":"3","parent":"1","text":"Caracterizada por dolor de cuello anterior, cambios transitorios\\Nde la función tiroidea trifásica y baja absorción de yodo-123","guid":"qTZZUCWe2YPKClnbVWlxRQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"4","parent":"0","text":"Causa","guid":"FIRbFA9P5AeRZ0NwXVVuUA","children":[{"id":"5","parent":"4","text":"Se desconoce la causa definitiva","guid":"mvl_cIAskKc2RBApBQEZPg","children":[]},{"id":"6","parent":"4","text":"Infecciones virales (que se producen de 2 a 6\\Nsemanas antes del inicio) son una causa probable","guid":"k1IjBpMo8HalkTNxx83iKg","children":[{"id":"7","parent":"6","text":"Tendencia de la enfermedad a seguir la infección","guid":"gbKJ1OB-plTUAIBbi6ZONg","children":[]},{"id":"8","parent":"6","text":"Cultivo viral positivo de tejido tiroideo","guid":"0L8BcBrDk40lO0jsNIXRrA","children":[]},{"id":"9","parent":"6","text":"Asociación de la tiroiditis subaguda con el prodrome viral","guid":"8gtXf8uktwLBDF2ZuPu6Sw","children":[]},{"id":"10","parent":"6","text":"Tendencia idéntica de distribución estacional con infecciones enterovirales establecidas\\N(ecovirus y virus Coxsackie A y B)","guid":"nMSkV1Sapyny7EbzXVx0Hw","children":[]},{"id":"11","parent":"6","text":"Tasas más altas de enfermedad durante las epidemias virales","guid":"HADOiM90tpU35bO6S0hlFw","children":[]}]},{"id":"12","parent":"4","text":"HLA-B35","guid":"EqmX4o-6Ufwt60M9qAUWIQ","children":[{"id":"13","parent":"12","text":"Puede conferir susceptibilidad a las infecciones virales y,\\Ndar lugar a un mayor riesgo de tiroiditis subaguda.","guid":"UKAvnN4q1QhcTl1nFPC0lg","children":[]}]},{"id":"14","parent":"4","text":"Medicamentos","guid":"kMYDxV5kNU4Y9tlf3KN_wA","children":[{"id":"15","parent":"14","text":"Alemtuzumab, los inhibidores del factor de necrosis tumoral (TNF) y\\Nel peginterferón alfa-2a, son posibles causas de tiroiditis subaguda.","guid":"_gnoRVoQMJcKsIkmRyQ6bQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"16","parent":"4","text":"Infección por COVID-19 son particularmente\\Nsusceptibles a la tiroiditis subaguda.","guid":"ru_wn4Yack_a9KF36JB48g","children":[]}]},{"id":"17","parent":"0","text":"Suele seguir un curso\\Nclínico trifásico","guid":"kOq7_PGcyazGqUSHqvD8jw","children":[{"id":"18","parent":"17","text":"Fase tirotóxica inicial\\N(hipertiroidea)","guid":"OgBN-XMPwZix3Tv0ZWx2UA","children":[{"id":"19","parent":"18","text":"General","guid":"a2Lxjt6Y9_o53r0wESLgng","children":[{"id":"20","parent":"19","text":"Alrededor del 50 %","guid":"92e7BRsKf1ebv1Dvwgadyg","children":[]},{"id":"21","parent":"19","text":"Normalmente persiste durante 3-6 semanas.","guid":"sIJ7NGK8KeYfKE92J3BccA","children":[]}]},{"id":"22","parent":"18","text":"Clinica","guid":"D2z96R4KHL-06wF0Ev0Jeg","children":[{"id":"23","parent":"22","text":"Fiebre baja","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"24","parent":"22","text":"Síntomas similares\\Na los de la gripe","guid":"mopqe2JAW2mAey1LO78DHg","children":[{"id":"25","parent":"24","text":"Dolor de garganta, mialgia,\\Nartralgia y malestar","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"26","parent":"22","text":"Dolor de cuello","guid":"CNvmZmdvuAXZmtaH9quTkw","children":[{"id":"27","parent":"26","text":"Generalmente se presenta unilateralmente\\Ny luego migra al lado opuesto.","guid":"kATpSjDOzR09DTKZc1GyKA","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"26","text":"Puede irradiar a la mandíbula, el oído,\\Nel occipucio y/o el pecho ipsilaterales.","guid":"tuAQwRVW3TcKjdrNXbsvRA","children":[]}]},{"id":"29","parent":"22","text":"Bocio ligeramente\\Nagrandado","guid":"Fe5KVVA4Ves5SyJKlDdGMg","children":[]},{"id":"30","parent":"22","text":"Tirotoxicosis","guid":"vT1ARaVkfVt3pWLUBnhM-g","children":[{"id":"31","parent":"30","text":"Puede estar presente","guid":"4fwAO8Ngc6aygVGgpxs_Rg","children":[]},{"id":"32","parent":"30","text":"Gravedad baja\\Na moderada","guid":"XyEl-kQ4atdxbmJM22C_HA","children":[{"id":"33","parent":"32","text":"Nerviosismo, pérdida de peso,\\Ntemblor y palpitaciones.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"34","parent":"30","text":"Laboratorio","guid":"","children":[{"id":"35","parent":"34","text":"TSH suprimida","guid":"TjkQlsSdH2GrmfRVJ5Ne8w","children":[]},{"id":"36","parent":"34","text":"Niveles elevados de tiroxina libre (T4)\\Ny triyodotironina (T3)","guid":"a_Cjyp-Libn8jqopmThOgw","children":[]}]}]}]}]},{"id":"37","parent":"17","text":"Fase hipotiroidea\\Nposterior","guid":"1p0nKqLIpO56GkE3U42cjw","children":[{"id":"38","parent":"37","text":"General","guid":"","children":[{"id":"39","parent":"38","text":"Alrededor del 25 % al 30 %","guid":"Th7CIMb4OXnKFq2PUTTzjQ","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"38","text":"Puede persistir hasta 6 meses","guid":"f3ltxPa-UPO6IDAhhjbYxQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"41","parent":"37","text":"Clínica","guid":"","children":[{"id":"42","parent":"41","text":"Dolor de tiroides, la fiebre y los síntomas tirotóxicos suelen resolverse.","guid":"iWicFZ_Kye627LP1AgMVnQ","children":[]},{"id":"43","parent":"41","text":"Un bocio pequeño puede estar presente.","guid":"JHMIlRkps4wetT7OML7nIA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"44","parent":"17","text":"Estado eutiroideo","guid":"0Dkhq4ID4kLPRWxNG6PvNw","children":[{"id":"45","parent":"44","text":"Más del 90 % de los pacientes","guid":"7_Fk0SodgNWSOIdMPIHttQ","children":[]},{"id":"46","parent":"44","text":"Pocas semanas o unos meses","guid":"twxMF6_haWqmlomPsMUwQQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"47","parent":"0","text":"Laboratorio","guid":"ZYN7ddbWhpqsLvMzTWLbyw","children":[{"id":"48","parent":"47","text":"Realizar pruebas de función tiroidea en pacientes con sospecha\\Nde tiroiditis subaguda para determinar la fase de la enfermedad","guid":"QgB_Eq5Yr9GMPYlAUdc5Kw","children":[]},{"id":"49","parent":"47","text":"Durante la fase\\Ntirotóxica","guid":"bezKsThL4VO-OR3AYxQeDw","children":[{"id":"50","parent":"49","text":"TSH pueden ser bajos.","guid":"Gguk5YGNfAt06jqkRIWk5A","children":[]},{"id":"51","parent":"49","text":"T4 y T3 pueden estar elevados\\N(relación T3:T4 generalmente < 20).","guid":"sxxUijtXZ67zcVxQE1jliQ","children":[]},{"id":"52","parent":"49","text":"T4 pueden ser normales si la tiroiditis subaguda\\Nafecta solo a una parte de la glándula tiroides.","guid":"XK261nFQoskB0VUViBvV1A","children":[]}]},{"id":"53","parent":"47","text":"Durante la fase\\Nhipotiroidea","guid":"w2IHaQ1IfcuVYyFzEnKJdg","children":[{"id":"54","parent":"53","text":"TSH pueden ser elevados.","guid":"LHKmu3THalYXIIQ1xgLl9w","children":[]},{"id":"55","parent":"53","text":"T4 y T3 pueden ser bajos.","guid":"buw7a_g0dMaD1eONbPCWeA","children":[]},{"id":"56","parent":"53","text":"Anticuerpos\\Nantitiroideos","guid":"p2o89HOyUDtLG-li4KhVhQ","children":[{"id":"57","parent":"56","text":"Anticuerpos contra la tiroglobulina, la tiroperoxidasa y el receptor TSH","guid":"GhKwte8Kj099A0oGNoD_1w","children":[]},{"id":"58","parent":"56","text":"Ayudar a diferenciar la tiroiditis subaguda de la tiroiditis autoinmune.","guid":"oCcYH3Bw-UJtN0768ZKiTQ","children":[]},{"id":"59","parent":"56","text":"Suelen estar\\Nausentes","guid":"yJ70VZhgTX5RGkTrJJ0MPg","children":[{"id":"60","parent":"59","text":"Niveles transitorios ligeramente elevados\\Nse informan en ≤ 25% de los pacientes","guid":"ZFnkz1rEbRxhz2O0iN2tFQ","children":[]},{"id":"61","parent":"59","text":"Posiblemente\\Ndebido a","guid":"-vqbINVECV2Rpr5DQufhOA","children":[{"id":"62","parent":"61","text":"Liberación de antígenos tiroideos cuando la glándula tiroides está dañada","guid":"KLG_p37BiYH5n6lKfL055A","children":[]},{"id":"63","parent":"61","text":"Resultado de la superposición de la enfermedad tiroidea autoinmune","guid":"putrraCXm-BUuUB8cfZyqw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"64","parent":"56","text":"Sospecha de tiroiditis autoinmune (tiroiditis de Hashimoto o enfermedad de Graves)\\Nsi se detectan títulos de anticuerpos muy altos.","guid":"pH7czrIEw8BPRmlvQCBbfw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"65","parent":"47","text":"Considere las pruebas de COVID-19 en pacientes con tiroiditis subaguda, ya que la disfunción\\Ntiroidea puede ser el único síntoma de una infección asintomática por COVID-19","guid":"thIwHIai7FKQnO72FDOxVw","children":[]}]},{"id":"66","parent":"0","text":"Imágenes ","guid":"","children":[{"id":"67","parent":"66","text":"Gammagrafía\\Ntiroidea","guid":"-7Jp8s6tKi0i9-0jC7h4nA","children":[{"id":"68","parent":"67","text":"Prueba de imagen preferida para determinar\\Nla causa de los bajos niveles de TSH","guid":"BW4uLDVaMBwZtlxWZSaRdg","children":[]},{"id":"69","parent":"67","text":"Absorción de yodo radiactivo varía\\Nsegún la fase de la enfermedad","guid":"W_a_Z4_6OMoFc3Hv4hV6-g","children":[{"id":"70","parent":"69","text":"Fase tirotóxica","guid":"xzsJaad9pE3UedUlpr4b6Q","children":[{"id":"71","parent":"70","text":"Absorción suele ser baja debido a la\\Ninterrupción de los folículos tiroideos","guid":"XpgIeZ54hLtssqKV6ZGnQA","children":[]},{"id":"72","parent":"70","text":"Si la absorción es elevada,\\Nsospeche la enfermedad de Graves","guid":"ae2HScXxvvc2n5PWbc734Q","children":[]}]},{"id":"73","parent":"69","text":"Fase hipotiroidea","guid":"0rrYDomNg6LeKNdqj9ahWw","children":[{"id":"74","parent":"73","text":"Absorción suele ser elevada","guid":"ClZLOvFO6VQaLG7SK70sLQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"75","parent":"69","text":"La absorción de yodo radiactivo puede ser normal si la\\Ntiroiditis subaguda solo afecta a una parte de la tiroides.","guid":"StneRC7qMksUS_sF_-yqjg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"76","parent":"66","text":"Ecografía tiroidea","guid":"0zf_Y1-69Uj-XEhXorBXhg","children":[{"id":"77","parent":"76","text":"No se utiliza de forma rutinaria","guid":"5eM7ZvK8AA0pSORRHObYXA","children":[]},{"id":"78","parent":"76","text":"Indicada\\Nante","guid":"Y_6oaUSKMraFMyDnfNA-UQ","children":[{"id":"79","parent":"78","text":"Sospecha de tiroiditis infecciosa aguda","guid":"afHVfaOpMjBdkBqabVr6yg","children":[]},{"id":"80","parent":"78","text":"Malignidad de la tiroides","guid":"qWTeMLeHK1nqYLP6FjlwNw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"81","parent":"66","text":"Biopsia por aspiración\\Ncon aguja fina (FNA)","guid":"MoGWNFRQqJwLbZsup1_22g","children":[{"id":"82","parent":"81","text":"Utilizar si el diagnóstico está en duda","guid":"84bTS_e76DSvuiNg2PUGCA","children":[]},{"id":"83","parent":"81","text":"Sospecha no aclarada\\Ntras ecografía de","guid":"EuoM_HNsiKCi8fNoDeqGpw","children":[{"id":"84","parent":"83","text":"Tiroiditis infecciosa aguda","guid":"4ndVP-vLAEkL4itlHvXuTw","children":[]},{"id":"85","parent":"83","text":"Malignidad tiroidea","guid":"jP1-CRuRkKoneORG2-Ey6A","children":[]},{"id":"86","parent":"83","text":"Implicación unilateral por sangrado\\Nen un quiste o neoplasia","guid":"VCHcO0X8r6tsamTFX2bGEg","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"87","parent":"0","text":"Manejo ","guid":"GuglzJzrK1CNY_QkYZaKYw","children":[{"id":"88","parent":"87","text":"Asintomática","guid":"G6vvk5-OnNcQ8p2zq32H9Q","children":[{"id":"89","parent":"88","text":"No se necesita tratamiento","guid":"oia2VbJSbM0fLqE9PO4IUQ","children":[]},{"id":"90","parent":"88","text":"Suele ser autolimitada","guid":"wh3tc0x0sVMFIP8QuCNhzw","children":[]}]},{"id":"91","parent":"87","text":"Síntomas","guid":"tlI0Is15qJivqlpHB8SqFQ","children":[{"id":"92","parent":"91","text":"Aliviar el dolor\\Nde tiroides","guid":"507Am1olXYW6mqMwE1ZbKg","children":[{"id":"93","parent":"92","text":"Utilice medicamentos antiinflamatorios no esteroideos\\N(AINE)","guid":"KAZGsu5XrBPisRhR0CCNcA","children":[{"id":"94","parent":"93","text":"Ibuprofeno de 1.200-3. 200 mg/día por vía oral en dosis divididas.","guid":"XlU-OOonhq5pyEQlKGwxzA","children":[]},{"id":"95","parent":"93","text":"La mediana del tiempo para la resolución del dolor es de 5 semanas\\N(rango de 1 a 20 semanas).","guid":"srK7WUzdXj5suxic--1w_g","children":[]}]},{"id":"96","parent":"92","text":"Corticoides","guid":"","children":[{"id":"97","parent":"96","text":"Prednisona 15-40 mg/día durante 1-6 semanas, luego se reduce.","guid":"5teIzhDdZI2peASzI7zehQ","children":[]},{"id":"98","parent":"96","text":"Considerar si los síntomas no mejoran en los pocos días","guid":"C89E4qdjy4OvO89b7ZbfZw","children":[]},{"id":"99","parent":"96","text":"Terapia alternativa\\Nde primera línea","guid":"HLhaXINWSrVxOk4kvpT08g","children":[{"id":"100","parent":"99","text":"Dolor de moderado a severo","guid":"dCsN-C46Gc0sYfurkPfjyg","children":[]},{"id":"101","parent":"99","text":"Síntomas tirotóxicos","guid":"M7yFiSkH2oeK3A2kt13MZA","children":[]}]},{"id":"102","parent":"96","text":"Suele dar lugar a una\\Nrespuesta marcada.","guid":"r4pqFoMkaAoevqUS2GOn6w","children":[{"id":"103","parent":"102","text":"Si la dosis se reduce demasiado rápido, los síntomas\\Npueden reaparecer y se debe aumentar la dosis.","guid":"s6eeZi_JU2TPTP0O0G5ezA","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"104","parent":"91","text":"Mejorar los síntomas\\Nde la tirotoxicosis","guid":"zA3NAX7jMHClZA1OTGl_8g","children":[{"id":"105","parent":"104","text":"Betabloqueantes\\N(propranolol o atenolol)","guid":"pGvTorWbdlVpmIzdJBeBDA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"106","parent":"87","text":"Levotiroxina","guid":"0nyeTlovqfj6p8GV3DGWuA","children":[{"id":"107","parent":"106","text":"Tratamiento en la fase hipotiroidea","guid":"EeX4oHop3K7dOUrowM6R8g","children":[]},{"id":"108","parent":"106","text":"Debe retirarse de 3-6 meses después de verificar la\\Nfunción tiroidea normal con pruebas de función tiroidea","guid":"Qd0KeHASMGl1umGCmC1Sng","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"109","parent":"0","text":"Seguimiento","guid":"","children":[{"id":"110","parent":"109","text":"Pruebas de\\Nfunción tiroidea","guid":"e_nJqp1rfOvYBJ7lrp5-UA","children":[{"id":"111","parent":"110","text":"Puede producirse hipotiroidismo\\Nde aparición tardía","guid":"XTXybjQgYNLqf5yODZEbtg","children":[]}]},{"id":"112","parent":"109","text":"Puede\\Nreaparecer","guid":"qIBPWRD8ek59GZZbFmNzyQ","children":[{"id":"113","parent":"112","text":"Durante un período de meses en algunos pacientes","guid":"yGhGreUY4Af0i1PJP2GrkQ","children":[]},{"id":"114","parent":"112","text":"Generalmente con una gravedad decreciente","guid":"1NhirKL1e3JD0eJfnGE5Sg","children":[]},{"id":"115","parent":"112","text":"El manejo de la recurrencia de la enfermedad\\Nes el mismo que el tratamiento inicial","guid":"VVmLeNNjc_PCV2Msy12zGg","children":[]}]}]}]},"node_count":115,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"General","folder":"Entidades clínicas","filename":"- Tiroiditis Subaguda","id":"map_104","resolved_references":[]}